Package sndlib.core.problem

Class Summary
DemandFlow A DemandFlow is used to represent the flow between the source and the target node of a single demand in a network with respect to a specific solution.
DemandLinkFlow A DemandLinkFlow is used to represent the flow on a single link incurred by a certain demand w.r.t. a specific solution.
DemandPathFlow A DemandPathFlow represents the flow on a single path incurred by a certain demand w.r.t. a specific solution.
LinkFlow A LinkFlow is used to represent the flow on a single link in a network with respect to a specific solution.
OperatingState This class represents an operating state in a survivable network design instance.
Problem A Problem couples a Network with a Model.
RoutingLink A RoutingLink is a component of a RoutingPath and wraps a single network link together with the direction of the corresponding flow.
RoutingPath This class represents a routing path in a specific solution of a network design problem.
RoutingPath.Builder This inner class abstracts the four static methods of RoutingPath.
SolvedProblem This class connects a specific Solution to a network design Problem.
 

Enum Summary
OperatingState.Type Lists the admissible types of an operating state.
